      "updated": "2026-06-05",
      "notes": "Promotes candidate slug maxent-spectrum. Study pass done 2026-06-05. Four implementations found across references, three distinct methods: (1) MULTIMAX lineage = WiMDA Wimdamax.pas AND Mantid MuonMaxent/MaxentTools (same FORTRAN ancestor, near-identical — implement ONCE, never offer as separate user choices); (2) Mantid generic MaxEnt-v1 (Skilling-Bryan, PosNeg entropy, complex images — genuinely different but Mantid's muon GUI dropped it in v3.12; do not expose as second engine, keep core seam engine-shaped); (3) WiMDA src/MaxEnt.pas is Burg all-poles MEM, NOT MaxEnt — excluded, naming hazard. musrfit has NO MaxEnt (roadmap item only; its PFTPhaseCorrection entropy code is FFT phase correction). WARNING: WiMDA's own FEATURE_MAP/SYMBOL_MAP 'maxent-spectrum' entries point at the Burg code and miss Wimdamax.pas entirely — do not navigate by them. Mantid MaxentTools is GPL-3: usable as verification oracle, must not be copied into MIT Asymmetry. Decision: port MULTIMAX with WiMDA as behavioral contract, Mantid numpy port as oracle."
